# Adversary fixture: FM4-b — blank node label ending in a dot
# Hypothesis: _:b1. is INVALID; the grammar's trailing PN_CHARS constraint
#   forbids a label ending in '.'.  A greedy regex like [A-Za-z0-9._-]+
#   will absorb the '.' into the label and misparse the statement
#   terminator, producing wrong output or silently accepting.
# Expected outcome: reject  (or accept with divergent bnode label)
outcome: reject
fact-count: 0
divergence-hypothesis: AcceptRejectSplit — greedy-regex parsers accept and misparse
spec-ref: W3C RDF 1.1 N-Triples §2.2 BLANK_NODE_LABEL — trailing PN_CHARS constraint
